    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5723381>
    dc:description "FIGURE 10. Pulvinaria nipponica Lindinger, 1933, adult female collected from Tokyo, Japan in 1965.ANT, antenna:AP, anal plate; DA, dermal areolation; DMD, dorsal microduct; DS, dorsal seta; DTD, dorsal tubular duct; LG, leg; MP, multilocular pores; MS, marginal seta; POP, preopercular pores; SDP, spiracular disc pore; SSP, stigmatic spines; VMD, ventral microduct; VTD, ventral tubular ducts, types I to III. Scale bars: 200 μm for ANT, DA and LG, 100 μm for AP, 50 μm for MS and SSP, and 10 μm for all other features." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5723381/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

